@node "Intr" "Introduction"

The Yam User Adminstration program is for heavy duty mail users. Yam 1.3,
a great mailer programmed by Marcel Beck, is now capable of maintaining 
several configfiles and mailboxes but lacks a little in the management 
of all those different mailboxes. Since I own several accounts on the 
Internet, it was desirable to have a little program for maintaining these 
mailboxes. So, the idea to program the Yam User Administration (YUAdmin) 
was born.

YUadmin is totally programmed in E, a great language developed by
Wouter van Oortmerssen.

I hope you enjoy my little program (and first ever published!).

Regards,

Bert Vortman

p.s. Send your bug reports to: BertVortman@www.dsdelft.nl

@endnode

@node "Reqs" "Requirements"

You need:

- Reqtools.library in the Libs: directory (supplied with YUAdmin)
- YAM 1.3+ (there is no point in using YUAdmin without Yam... or is it??)
- Everything Yam uses... (AMITCP, MUI etc.)

@endnode

