@node "Inst" "Installation"

 @{b}INSTALLATION USING THE COMMODORE-INSTALLER@{ub}

 Double click on the @{b}Install@{ub} icon and follow
 the instructions of the Installer.

 @{b}MANUAL INSTALLATION@{ub}

 Installation couldn't be easier:

 1) Copy the YUAdmin program to the YAM: directory. 
    (You must have an assignment to @{b}YAM:@{ub}!) 

 2) Make a MAIL directory in YAM: This directory will contain all the
    mailfolders for your accounts. (allthough you can use an other 
    directory if you want, see usage)

 3) copy the reqtools.library to LIBS:

 4) copy the newtopaz.font and directory to FONTS:

    That's all.

@endnode


@node "Usag" "Usage"
 @{b}USAGE@{ub}

 YUAdmin is easy to use, no difficult commands have to be learned.

 When you start YUAdmin the first time by doubleclicking it's icon 
 YUAdmin will ask you if you want to configure a user. If you want to,
 you will be presented with a listview and 3 buttons: 'Add user',
 'Delete user' and 'Cancel'. Since you want to Add a user, (are you?)
 click on the appropiate button.

 Two stringgadgets are presented, one for the username and the other
 one for the directory where your mailfolders are stored.
 You can use different directory's for different accounts, but you
 can not use the same username twice, even if you have two different
 directory's.

 Click on Add User, you will be asked if everything is correct, if so,
 click on yes. Some files are written to disk and a requester will
 inform you if everything went ok. You will be presented with
 the mainwindow of YUAdmin.

 The middle section of the window is for all your users. On a 256*640
 screen you can have more than 50 users (depending on the font you
 use). The bigger the screen, the more users you can have. (Experimenting
 I had more than 300 users.... ;) ) The program tries to display as much
 users as it can.

 Just click on the users name to enter YAM. YAM will use immediately
 the correct config file and directory's. The first time you need
 to configure the user's settings in the configuration menu. Save it the
 usual way, and everything is ready to use. If you quit YAM, the
 YUAdmin window is displayed again, waiting for your actions. 

 The 'Add & Delete' button will display the initial listview. To delete
 a user, click on the user's name in the listview to select and click
 on the appropiate button. 

 FONTS
 -----

 YUAdmin is capable of handling different fonts. Select the appropiate
 menu item to select a font. However, only the users names will use
 the font.

@endnode

